    <p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Dr Jiwa Mohd Isa</strong></span><br />
    ADVISOR<br />
    <br />
    Jiwa Mohd Isa studied International Business &amp; Finance at the New Mexico State University, USA and thereafter obtained his Masters in International Management in International Finance and Banking from the American Graduate School of International Management (Thunderbird), USA.&nbsp; He gained lecturing, consulting and administrative experiences from the International Islamic University Malaysia before completing his PhD in Management Control Systems at Manchester Business School, University of Manchester in 1994.<br />
    <br />
    Having more than 26 years of robust management and consulting experiences, he acquired specialized entrepreneurial and intrapreneurial skills in diverse industries which included private tertiary education, agribusiness, financial, software application, property development, and construction industries.&nbsp; He has played a significant role in the growth of numerous companies in the Middle East and Malaysia.<br />
    <br />
    Since 1995 he architected and instrumental in establishing a virtual university, a campus-based private university, two private colleges and turnaround 3 private institutions.&nbsp; Correspondingly, he also initiated diverse start-ups businesses in feedlot cattle, factoring, and software application companies.&nbsp; His other consulting activities entail the conduct of feasibility studies and production of proposals for acquisition or establishment of potential projects such as alternative energy, hotel &amp; resort, integrated farming, feedlot cattle and private security services.<br />
    <br />
    His success in his managerial and consulting roles came from his ability to accurately evaluate strategy, management, financial strength and systems of companies in diverse businesses.<br />
    &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
    <p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Ir. Md Jafrry Masat</strong><br />
    EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR</span></p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Ir. Md. Jafrry Bin Masat obtained his first degree in Civil Engineering at the Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology (RMIT), Australia and later&nbsp;persued his MBA at the International Islamic University (IIU)Malaysia.&nbsp; He is registered as Professional Engineer (P.Eng) with the&nbsp;Board of Engineers, Malaysia (BEM). He is a member of&nbsp; Association of Consulting Engineers Malaysia (ACEM) and Institute of Engineers Malaysia (IEM). He is the Principal of Edara Consult Engineer, Executive Director of <span style="font-family: Arial;">Edara <span style="line-height: 115%; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">Strategic Consultancy Sdn Bhd and Director of a construction firm Sweet Theme Sdn Bhd.</span><br />
    </span></p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Ir. Md Jafrry has more than 18 years of vast experience in project supervision, project engineering, project management, project proposals, project tendering and project design in the utility and construction industries.&nbsp; Capitalizing his competencies in both technical and non-technical areas, Ir. Md. Jafrry has conducted various trainings and staff development programs. He has contributed significantly in numerous civil/infrastructure and building project throughout his career as a Professional Engineer.&nbsp; His interpersonal skills are of profound value to his organization when managing small to large project teams and dealing with local Authorities&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Ir.&nbsp;Mohd Zaki bin Saleh</strong><br />
    EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR</span></p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Ir. Mohd Zaki bin Saleh obtained his Degree in Electrical Electronic Engineering from the University of Iwate, Japan. He is registered as Professional Engineer (P.Eng) with Board of Engineers, Malaysia (BEM) and a 33kV Competent Engineer to SuruhanjayaTenaga Malaysia.</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">With over 16 years of enormous experience in project implementation, operation and maintenance, trading, after sales and service of power transmission and distribution system for TNB, SESCo, SESB, KKLW (BELB), Rapid KL (PUTRA), Oil and Gas and other commercial sector, Ir. MohdZaki has contributed significantly to the power Transmission and Distribution System industry. His ideas, knowledge and involvement had a significant effect in expediting the projects on a timely delivery. His charm and capabilities in managing people from all walks of life namely from labourers, contractors vendors right up to dealing with clients and authorities, is of a great asset to his organization&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Laili Mohd Isa<br />
    </strong>DIRECTOR, CORPORATE SERVICES</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Laili has a BBA from the International Islamic University Malaysia and later obtained a MBA at the University Science of Malaysia in 1996. She is currently pursuing her Doctor of Business Administration at Multimedia University.<br />
    &nbsp;<br />
    With over&nbsp;19 years of industry experience, Laili gained a reputation for expanding customer relationships and developing quality standards, doing so for a client base ranging from small entrepreneurial to large corporations.&nbsp; She has served in large Multinational Corporation such as Ingress Corporation, Esso Production (Malaysia) and Quantum in areas of corporate communications, business development, planning and procurement.&nbsp; Her most recent position in a virtual university is Head of Corporate Services.</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Throughout her professional career, Laili has significant strategic and operations experiences in organizational development, customer relationships as well as experience developing businesses and leading globalization plans.<br />
    &nbsp;<br />
    Laili is also known for building effective work teams and developing her leadership teams&rsquo; talent.&nbsp; As a Corporate Services Head of a virtual university, she was one of the driving forces in educating multi-cultural employees throughout the organization in cost disciplines and setting congruence effective work objectives.<br />
    &nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Dr Nurol&rsquo;ain Mustapha</strong><br />
    </span>CONSULTANT<br />
    <br />
    With more than 24 years of lecturing, research and development, training and consultancy experiences in areas of services management, organizational development, knowledge management, organizational behavior and management systems, Dr Nurol&rsquo;ain has assisted companies of various sizes to matched their products, services and internal processes with customer needs in order to achieve desired financial and operational performances. She has a vast experience in conducting and supervising research papers in her field of expertise.</p>
    <p><span style="font-family: Arial;">Dr Nurol&rsquo;ain obtained her BBA from California State University at Fresno, MBA at the National University Malaysia and PhD in Managerial Work from University of Surrey, UK.<br />
    &nbsp;</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Alias Kassim</strong><br />
    </span>CONSULTANT<br />
    <br />
    Alias Kassim has a BSc in Electrical Engineering majoring in Computer Engineering from the University of Texas, El Paso, U.S.A. and later obtained a MBA at the Open University Malaysia.&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;</span></p>
    <div><span style="font-family: Arial;">With almost 23 years serving the IT industry, Alias has acquired extensive experience in creating and formulating IT infrastructure from drafting of blueprint right up to the implementation and operations of Mission Critical Data Centres inclusive of Disaster Recovery Planning (DRP) for one of Malaysia&rsquo;s prominent Statutory Organisation. In leveraging further his acquired skills, he dedicated himself as one of the aspiring team members in the setup and implementation of world first Virtual Islamic University in which his main contribution was the formulation of the University&rsquo;s e-Learning components and its online delivery methods.&nbsp;</span></div>
    <div align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;</span></div>
    <div><span style="font-family: Arial;">Known for his strategic thinking, dynamic interpersonal and leadership skills, Alias contributed significantly towards the growth and success of the organisations he served. His success in implementing strategies through adopting emerging technologies to create cutting edge competitive advantage, effective projects implementation, and efficient operations.</span></div>
